description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for an experienced and proactive Medical Secretary to join the Elderly Care Department at SBU Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Secretary will be responsible for proving comprehensive secretarial support to the Elderly Care Department, maintaining a direct and close working relationship with the Consultant/Medical staff, Nursing Team, Medical Secretaries as well as other support staff within the Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This challenging position requires someone who has experience of working on their own initiative, who is a team player, flexible, organised and is able to work well under pressure. The successful candidate will need to be an experienced typist, qualified to RSA Typing/Word Processing Level III (or equivalant qualification). This position also requires good communication skills, the ability to meet the demands of working in a busy environment and is able to represent the department with due professionalism.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have drive and enthusiasm, and are suitably qualified, this post will offer an exciting new challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diane WilliamsMedical Support Manager&lt;/p&gt;
